description:
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for rotational posts based at the Sheffield Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust. Applicants need to hold an appropriate Occupational Therapist qualification (BSc/Diploma in Occupational Therapy or equivalent), and be registered with the Health and Care Professions Council (HCPC). We welcome applications from students due to graduate this year.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for forward thinking Occupational Therapists who would like to be part of patient centred transformational service delivery which includes the development of integrated ward teams within key specialities. We offer rotations through the core areas of neurology, musculoskeletal and medicine along pathways of care within both the acute and community setting. Rotations cover a wide range of specialities which may include the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Orthopaedics, burns and plastics, cardiothoracic surgery, general surgery, acute medicine, care of the elderly, specialised medicine, spinal injuries, neurosurgery, neuro-medicine, stroke unit, community stroke.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Each rotation will be at either the Northern General Hospital, the Royal Hallamshire Hospital or in a community setting. Successful applicants will be involved in the delivery of 7 day services and shift patterns will vary according to speciality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This vacancy is advertised on a fixed term contract basis for the maximum period of 6 months. Where there is potential, the secondment/fixed term contract may finish early, or in the first instance, the secondment/fixed term contract may be extended due to the internal/external secondment of the substantive post holder. The fixed term contract status of the post holder will be reviewed in accordance with the Trust&#39;s legal obligations regarding fixed term contracts and secondments in relation to the substantive post holder&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Sarah Leighton (Clinical Service Manager)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Email: sarah.leighton2@nhs.net&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Tel: 0114 2269115&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the recruitment process at application stage, Sheffield Teaching Hospitals will assess applicants’ individual values and behaviours to ensure that these behaviours align with our PROUD values: Patient First, Respectful, Ownership, Unity and Deliver.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our values are what help to make us different and ‘a Brilliant Place to Work’. We expect all our employees to share our values and demonstrate them in every aspect of their role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to undertake an online values assessment at application stage and the results of this assessment will be used as part of the on-going selection process to assess your suitability for the post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The deadline for completing the online assessment is midnight 21/11/2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The link to the assessment can be found below, the address can be copied and pasted into a search engine e.g. google:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; login.talentqgroup.com/Login/SelfService/ERBRQXPRLW&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have any queries, require any assistance to complete this assessment or have already completed it within the past 12 months, please contact the Trust Recruitment Team at &lt;strong&gt;sth.centralrecruitment@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
